{"id":15,"parent_id":7,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":15,"title":"Matthew 8-9","subtitle":"","short_title":"Matthew 8-9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9"},[".heading",{"id":"head9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.head9"},["h1","Matthew 8–9"],[".subtitle","Jesus Performs Many Miracles"],[".intro","After Jesus taught His great Sermon on the Mount, He went among the people, teaching them and also performing many miracles. In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8"},"Matthew 8–9"],"is recorded several miracles Jesus performed while He was in the area near the Sea of Galilee."],[".",{"id":"f38","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f38"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-017-1.gif"}]],[".intro","What might be the importance of these miracles? Elder Bruce R. McConkie, who was a member of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles, taught that while most often “our Lord in his ministry is preaching the gospel of the kingdom; … announcing to all men what they must do to gain peace in this life and eternal life in the world to come,” the Savior also performed miracles, as “visible evidences in the eyes of all, believers and nonbelievers alike, that he has more than mortal power. They are proof, as it were, that his words are true” (Mortal Messiah, 2:42; see also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/11.3-5"},"Matthew 11:3–5"],"). Elder McConkie also taught that “miracles of themselves do not convert men to the truth. … But miracles may so impress the sincere investigator as to cause him to take the steps that lead to faith” (Doctrinal New Testament Commentary, 2:81)."],[".intro","As you read the accounts in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8"},"Matthew 8–9"],"of miracles Jesus performed, consider what they teach you about Jesus and ways each miracle could strengthen your faith and encourage you to more fully trust in Him."]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8"},"Matthew 8–9"]],["p.para",{"id":"p268","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p268"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.1-4"},"Matthew 8:1–4"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/1.40-45"},"Mark 1:40–45"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/5.12-16"},"Luke 5:12–16"]],["p.para",{"id":"p269","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p269"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.5-13"},"Matthew 8:5–13"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/7.1-10"},"Luke 7:1–10"]],["p.para",{"id":"p270","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p270"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.14-15"},"Matthew 8:14–15"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/1.29-31"},"Mark 1:29–31"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/4.38-39"},"Luke 4:38–39"]],["p.para",{"id":"p271","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p271"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.18-22"},"Matthew 8:18–22"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/9.57-62"},"Luke 9:57–62"]],["p.para",{"id":"p272","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p272"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.23-27"},"Matthew 8:23–27"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/4.35-41"},"Mark 4:35–41"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/8.22-25"},"Luke 8:22–25"]],["p.para",{"id":"p273","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p273"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.28-34"},"Matthew 8:28–34"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/5.1-20"},"Mark 5:1–20"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/8.26-39"},"Luke 8:26–39"]],["p.para",{"id":"p274","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p274"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.1-17"},"Matthew 9:1–17"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.1-22"},"Mark 2:1–22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/5.17-39"},"Luke 5:17–39"]],["p.para",{"id":"p275","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p275"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.18-26"},"Matthew 9:18–26"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/5.21-43"},"Mark 5:21–43"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/8.40-56"},"Luke 8:40–56"]],["p.para",{"id":"p276","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p276"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.35-38"},"Matthew 9:35–38"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/10.2-3"},"Luke 10:2–3"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f39","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f39"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8"},"Matthew 8"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Leper, leprosy"],"(vv. 2–3)"],["td","Leprosy refers to various diseases of the skin, tissues, or nerves (see also Bible Dictionary,",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/leper"},"“leper”"],"and",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bd/leprosy"},"“leprosy,”"],"pp. 723–24)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Centurion"],"(vv. 5, 8, 13)"],["td","A leader in the Roman army in charge of one hundred soldiers"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Palsy"],"(v. 6)"],["td","A disease that left a person disabled"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Grievously tormented"],"(v. 6)"],["td","In terrible pain"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Even"],"(v. 16)"],["td","Evening"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Infirmities"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Weaknesses"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Bare"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Carried"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Perish, perished"],"(vv. 25, 32)"],["td","Die"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rebuked"],"(v. 26)"],["td","Commanded to quit"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Torment"],"(v. 29)"],["td","Punish"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Swine"],"(vv. 30–32)"],["td","Pigs"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Besought"],"(vv. 31, 34)"],["td","Asked"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Befallen"],"(v. 33)"],["td","Happened"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.4"},"Matthew 8:4"],"—Why Would Jesus Tell Those He Healed to Not Tell Anyone about It?"],["p.para",{"id":"p290","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p290"},"See “Understanding the Scriptures” for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/16.20"},"Matthew 16:20"],"(p. 24)."]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.21-22"},"Matthew 8:21–22"],"—Why Wouldn’t Jesus Let the Man Bury His Father?"],["p.para",{"id":"p291","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p291"},"The following statement by Elder Bruce R. McConkie helps us understand why Jesus asked the man to follow Him rather than go and bury his father: “When men are called of God by the spirit of revelation, called in the omnipotent wisdom of him who knoweth all things, those calls take precedence over all conflicting interests. Missionaries so sent forth habitually forsake all personal and family obligations. Loved ones may pass away, but missionaries remain at their posts, preaching the kingdom of God” (",["span.emphasis","Doctrinal New Testament Commentary,"],"1:304)."],["p.para",{"id":"p292","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p292"},"It is important to remember that no matter the circumstance, we are to follow Christ."],[".figure",{"id":"f40","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f40"},["p"],["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9"},"Matthew 9"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","His own city"],"(v. 1)"],["td","Capernaum (see Bible Dictionary, “Capernaum,” p. 631)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Blasphemeth"],"(v. 3)"],["td","Speaks irreverently about sacred things"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Son of man"],"(v. 6)"],["td","Jesus called Himself the Son of Man because He is the Son of God the Father, and one of Heavenly Father’s names is “Man of Holiness” (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.57"},"Moses 6:57"],"). Therefore, Jesus is “Son of Man of Holiness.”"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Thence"],"(vv. 9, 27)"],["td","There"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Receipt of custom"],"(v. 9)"],["td","Place to collect taxes"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Sat at meat"],"(v. 10)"],["td","Was eating a meal"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Publicans"],"(vv. 10–11)"],["td","Tax collectors"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Oft"],"(v. 14)"],["td","Many times (short for",["span.emphasis","often"],")"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Children of the bridechamber"],"(v. 15)"],["td","Wedding guests"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Bridegroom"],"(v. 15)"],["td","Man who is getting married (often symbolic of Christ, and the woman is the Church)"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Garment"],"(vv. 16, 20)"],["td","Piece of clothing"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rent"],"(v. 16)"],["td","Tear"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Minstrels"],"(v. 23)"],["td","People who play music"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Give place"],"(v. 24)"],["td","Move away, make room"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Laughed him to scorn"],"(v. 24)"],["td","Made fun of him, were disrespectful"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Son of David"],"(v. 27)"],["td","A special name that shows they believed He was the descendant of King David who was to be their king, or Messiah, or Christ"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Dumb"],"(vv. 32–33)"],["td","Cannot speak"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Moved with compassion"],"(v. 36)"],["td","Felt kind, loving feelings; felt sorry"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Fainted"],"(v. 36)"],["td","Discouraged, weary"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Plenteous"],"(v. 37)"],["td","Many"],["td"]]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p313","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p313"},"Do three of the following activities (A–D) as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8"},"Matthew 8–9"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Great Examples of Faith"],[".",{"id":"f41","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f41"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-018-1.gif"}]],[".figure",{"id":"f42","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f42"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.5-13"},"Matthew 8:5–13"],"tells the story of a leader in the Roman army—a Gentile, not an Israelite—who sought help from the Savior. What did the Savior say in verse 10 about the centurion’s faith compared to the faith of the Israelites of that day?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","From what you read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/8.5-9"},"Matthew 8:5–9"],", explain at least two ways the centurion showed remarkable faith."]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","What did the woman in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.20-22"},"Matthew 9:20–22"],"and the men in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.27-29"},"Matthew 9:27–29"],"do to show their faith?"]],["li",["span.label","4."],["p.para","Choose an area of your life or a teaching of the gospel in which you would like to have more faith. How could the example of the centurion, the woman, or the two men help you increase your faith in that area?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-b.gif"}],"“Perhaps the Greatest Miracle”"],["p.para",{"id":"p318","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p318"},"Elder John A. Widtsoe, who was a member of the Quorum of the Twelve Apostles, said, “I have come to understand that perhaps the greatest miracle in the gospel of the Lord Jesus Christ is the transformation that comes to a man or a woman who in faith accepts the truth of the gospel and who then lives it in his or her life. … As new and greater truths come, as the understanding of them develops within us if we accept and live them, we are transformed from ordinary men into new powers and possibilities” (in Conference Report, Apr. 1952, 34)."],["p.para",{"id":"p319","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.p319"},"Among all the stories found in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9"},"Matthew 9"],", which do you think is perhaps the best example of the kind of miracle Elder Widtsoe spoke about? Why?"]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-c.gif"}],"When to See the Doctor"],[".figure",{"id":"f43","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f43"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","According to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.10-12"},"Matthew 9:10–12"],", who needs a doctor?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","How could these verses help you grow spiritually?"]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","How could they help you as you try to help another person join the Church or come back into activity?"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-d.gif"}],"Laborers Wanted"],[".figure",{"id":"f44","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-matthew/matthew-8-9.f44"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","According to",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.36-38"},"Matthew 9:36–38"],", how did Jesus feel? Why did He feel that way?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","Write an imaginary advertisement for a newspaper, asking for people to apply for this “labour” Jesus spoke of in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.36-38"},"Matthew 9:36–38"],". Include in the advertisement the qualifications you think Jesus would want of those who serve with Him."]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
